Hello,
> safe_mode and open_basedir usually use small providers. Of course, this
> is idiotic use safe_mode and open_basedir when we can bypass it via
> symlinks.
>   
The Hardened-PHP project already explained in 2006 that open_basedir and
symlink do not mix. It is a not fixable design problem. So any advisory
explaining how to bypass open_basedir with a symlink attack is just
repeating news from 4 years ago.

http://www.hardened-php.net/advisory_082006.132.html


Regards,
Stefan Esser

